# Documentation Structure

The documentation uses MDSvex for markdown processing with custom components. Key files:

- [svelte.config.js](mdc:svelte.config.js) - Contains MDSvex configuration with custom layouts and plugins
- [src/lib/mdsvex-layout.svelte](mdc:src/lib/mdsvex-layout.svelte) - Default MDSvex layout
- [src/routes/(documentation)/docs/mdsvex-layout.svelte](mdc:src/routes/(documentation)/docs/mdsvex-layout.svelte) - Documentation-specific layout
- [src/routes/(documentation)/docs/content/en/intro.svex](mdc:src/routes/(documentation)/docs/content/en/intro.svex) - Example documentation page

## Writing Documentation

Documentation pages:
1. Use `.svex` extension
2. Live in `src/routes/(documentation)/docs/content/[lang]/`
3. Support frontmatter for metadata
4. Can use custom components directly without imports
5. Support automatic table of contents via remark-toc
